Package: econGame
Title: Tools for in-class game experiments for Principles of Economics
Version: 0.0.1
Authors@R: 
    person(given = "James",
           family = "Bang",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "bangjamest@gmail.com",
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-7701-8220"))
Author: James Bang [aut, cre], 
Maintainer: James Bang <bangecon@gmail.com>    
Description: This package loads activity data from Microsoft Form submissions 
    to an Excel file; tabulates, scores, and graphs the responses; and writes 
    the grades to a separate Excel file. Supported games include 
      1.  Market equilibrium game; 
      2.  Ultimatum game; 
      3.  Anchoring game;
      4.  Entry and exit game; 
      5.  Monopoly license lottery auction game; 
      6.  Monopoly license all-pay auction game; 
      7.  Multi-player prisoner's dilemma game; 
      8.  Stag hunt game; 
      9.  Rock-paper-scissors; 
      10. Public good game; 
      11. Pollution policy game.
    All documentation files include links to Google Forms addresses that can be 
    copied and saved. 
